{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %}

Usage

{% raw %} 
class FooBar(CheckSumMixin):
    def some_method_returning_checksum(self, content):
        return self.calculate_checksum(content)


foobar = FooBar()
{% endraw %}

Tests

{% raw %} 
test_content = b"foobar"
assert (
    foobar.some_method_returning_checksum(test_content)
    == hashlib.md5(test_content).hexdigest()
)

class Epoch[source]

Epoch(file_size:int, duration:int=30, bandwidth:int=125000000, files:list[BenchmarkFile]=[], urls:list[str]=[], file_creator:Callable=FilesystemCreator(), data_root:str='data') :: BaseModel

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %}

Usage

{% raw %} 
byte = 8
hundred_mbit = 10 ** 8
bandwidth = hundred_mbit / byte
duration = 2  # seconds
file_size = 10 ** 6 * 3  # 100MB

epoch = Epoch(
    file_size=file_size,
    duration=duration,
    bandwidth=bandwidth,
    file_creator=DummyCreator(),
)
epoch.create_files()
print(len(epoch.files))

9
{% endraw %}

Tests

{% raw %} 
byte = 8
gigabit = 10 ** 9

test_params = {
    "file_size": 10 ** 6 * 10,  # 10MB
    "duration": 30,
    "bandwidth": gigabit / byte,
    "file_creator": DummyCreator(),
}

test_epoch = Epoch(**test_params)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
assert test_epoch.bandwidth == 125000000
assert test_epoch.number_of_files == 375
assert test_epoch.get_bytes_per_second(30.0) == test_epoch.bandwidth
assert test_epoch.number_of_connections == 13
assert "file_size" in test_epoch.json()
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
test_epoch.create_files()
assert len(test_epoch.files) == test_epoch.number_of_files

# assert we don't generate files twice
test_epoch.create_files()
assert len(test_epoch.files) == test_epoch.number_of_files
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
assert "file_creator" not in test_epoch.dict_without_file_creator()

class TestClient(BaseClient):
    measured: bool = False

    def measure(self, benchmark_row):
        self.measured = True
        print("measure_benchmark_row: ", benchmark_row)
        return 2.0


class TestServer(BaseServer):
    started: bool = False
    stopped: bool = False

    def start(self):
        self.started = True

    def stop(self):
        self.stopped = True


row_params = {
    "file_size": 10 ** 6 * 10,
    "duration": 30,
    "bandwidth": 10 ** 9 / 8,
    "file_creator": DummyCreator(),
}
epoch = Epoch(**row_params)

test_result = Result.build_empty_result(
    epoch, TestServer(name="server"), TestClient(name="client")
)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
assert test_result.server == "server"
assert test_result.client == "client"

Tests

{% raw %} 
%%time
from collections import namedtuple

TestPlatform = namedtuple("TestPlatform", ["machine"])
    
byte = 8
gigabit = 10 ** 9
file_sizes = [10 ** 7, 10 ** 6, 10 ** 5]

test_params = {
    "duration": 3,
    "bandwidth": gigabit / byte / 10,  # divided by ten for test duration
    "file_creator": DummyCreator(),
    "file_sizes": file_sizes,
    "cpuinfo": {"python_version": 4.0},
    "uname": TestPlatform("M3"),
    "repository": TestRepository(),
}

test_benchmark = Benchmark(**test_params)

test_benchmark.create_epochs()
assert len(test_benchmark.epochs) == len(file_sizes)

CPU times: user 11.4 ms, sys: 207 s, total: 11.6 ms
Wall time: 11.5 ms
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
%%time

class TestClient(BaseClient):
    measured: bool = False

    def measure(self, benchmark_row):
        self.measured = True
        print("measure_benchmark_row: ", benchmark_row)
        return 2.0


class TestServer(BaseServer):
    started: bool = False
    stopped: bool = False

    def start(self):
        self.started = True

    def stop(self):
        self.stopped = True


test_params = {
    **test_params,
    "clients": [TestClient(name="foo")],
    "servers": [TestServer(name="bar")],
}
test_benchmark = Benchmark(**test_params)
test_benchmark.create_epochs()
test_benchmark.run()
